Head wider than long ( Figs. 1 ,
13, 14
), almost convex, frontal and occipital regions clearly differentiated, with caudal margin concave; epicranial sutures weak; distance between eyes about 2.3 × length of right scapus; left scapus disproportionately small and evidently abnormal. Eyes large and prominent, about twice longer than length of head posterior to eyes (gena sensu
Hincks 1955
